  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey @Haroenv,\r\nIn my experience if we use reserved words in JS code (e.g. class) which are supposed to be keywords in ES6, YUI compressor fails. In one of the libraries I worked on, I found the same issue, and the root cause was I was using the cjs syntax and compiling the code to UMD. That added a default export like this:\r\n\r\n``exports.default = myLib``\r\n\r\nAgain ``default`` is another reserved word in ES6 which YUI compressor refuses to resolve. I don't think it has anything to do with ES3. Correct me if I am wrong!",
